                "code": "patient-description"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} is a lively and energetic 5-year-old boy who is brought into the clinic by his mother. He appears visibly uncomfortable, sitting quietly in his mother's lap — a stark contrast to his usually boisterous personality. His face is flushed, and he is intermittently tugging at his throat and wincing when he swallows. His eyes are glassy and slightly teary, and his voice is noticeably muffled, as if he is speaking with a mouth full of marbles. He is dressed in a dinosaur-themed shirt and clutches a small toy truck, though he shows little interest in playing with it today.\n\n{patientName} lives at home with his mother, father, and 7-year-old sister in a suburban neighborhood. He attends a local kindergarten full-time, where he is known for being outgoing and energetic. His mother reports that several children in his class have recently had similar illnesses, suggesting a possible cluster of infection at school.\n\nHe is a picky but generally healthy eater, enjoying pasta, fruit, and juice. He is fully up-to-date on his childhood vaccinations. He has no known chronic medical conditions and has only been to the emergency department once before, for a minor laceration on his chin from a playground fall. He typically sleeps 10 hours a night and is physically active, enjoying bike riding and playing in the backyard.\n\nHis mother reports that {patientName}'s symptoms began approximately 3 days ago with a sore throat and mild fever. Over the past 24 hours, his fever has increased to 38.9°C, and he has been refusing to eat solid food due to pain with swallowing. She notes he has been more irritable and fatigued than usual. She denies any rash, ear pain, difficulty breathing, or neck stiffness. No recent travel history."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
