        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} has no significant chronic medical history. He was born at full term via normal vaginal delivery without complications, and his developmental milestones have been met appropriately for his age. He had one episode of otitis media at age 3, which was treated successfully with a course of amoxicillin. He has had no previous episodes of tonsillitis or hospitalizations other than a minor ER visit for a chin laceration.\n\n{patientName}'s vaccination record is complete and up-to-date per the national immunization schedule, including MMR, varicella, pneumococcal, and influenza vaccines. He has no known allergies to medications or foods. His mother notes that his older sister had a streptococcal throat infection approximately one week ago and was treated with antibiotics. There is no family history of rheumatic fever or immune deficiency. {patientName} does not attend daycare but does attend a full-day kindergarten program, where close contact with other children increases his exposure to respiratory pathogens. He is a non-smoker household — neither parent smokes indoors."
          }
        ]
      }
